        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We evaluated <span class="accent">10 GBP analytics tools</span> on the 5 metrics that drive local ranking decisions.</h2>
      <p>We automate local SEO for 3,500+ businesses across 70+ industries. We know which data points drive local ranking improvements — and which are just dashboard noise. Every tool was evaluated on the same 5 criteria. No vendor demos, no sponsored placements, no affiliate deals.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria specific to GBP analytics.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Local SEO analytics that don't answer these 5 questions aren't worth paying for.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Maps rank tracking</h4>
              <p>Does it track your Google Maps position across geographic points? You cannot improve local rankings without knowing where you currently rank — neighborhood by neighborhood.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Performance metrics</h4>
              <p>Does it report impressions, clicks, calls, and direction requests over time? Trend data reveals what's working and what's not, month over month.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Review analytics</h4>
              <p>Does it track review volume, average rating, and response rate trends? Review velocity and rating trends directly impact local pack rankings.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Competitor benchmarking</h4>
              <p>Can you compare your GBP metrics against nearby competitors? Knowing your gap versus the #1 competitor tells you exactly how much ground to cover.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Reporting and exports</h4>
              <p>Does it produce shareable reports with actionable insights? Business owners and stakeholders need clear data — not raw dashboards.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Analytics tools show the gap. theStacc closes it.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The key finding from testing all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Native GBP Insights is insufficient for serious local SEO</h4>
              <p>GBP Insights provides basic impressions and clicks. It cannot show Maps rankings across a geographic radius, compare against competitors, or audit your profile for optimization gaps. A dedicated analytics tool is required.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Geo-grid tracking is the highest-leverage local analytics feature</h4>
              <p>Knowing that you rank #1 within 0.5 miles but fall to #8 at 2 miles tells you exactly where to invest in local optimization. Businesses with geo-grid data make better local SEO decisions than those relying on aggregate rankings.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Review analytics is underrated</h4>
              <p>Review velocity (how fast you're accumulating reviews) is one of the strongest local ranking signals. Most businesses don't track it. Tools that surface review trends give a competitive advantage that most local businesses miss.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Analytics without action is waste</h4>
              <p>The tools that tell you you're ranking #6 don't post to GBP for you. They don't respond to reviews. They don't submit citations. theStacc is the only platform in this category that both tracks your performance and automatically improves it.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
