      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best GBP analytics tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the best for local businesses that want GBP analytics combined with automated posting, review responses, and citation management from $49/month. For standalone analytics with the deepest data, BrightLocal at $39/month covers geo-grid tracking, GBP audits, citation monitoring, and review analytics. Local Falcon at $24.99/month is the best for pure geo-grid Maps rank tracking.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does a GBP analytics tool measure?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">GBP analytics tools measure impressions, clicks, phone calls, direction requests, Maps rankings across geographic points, review volume, rating trends, response rates, photo views, and competitor benchmarking. Native GBP Insights covers basic impressions and clicks but cannot show Maps rankings across a geographic radius or compare metrics against competitors.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is geo-grid Maps rank tracking?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Geo-grid rank tracking shows your Google Maps ranking at dozens of geographic points across a customizable radius around your business. The result is a color-coded heatmap showing where you rank #1 and where you're invisible. A business might rank first within 0.5 miles but fall to #8 at 2 miles — without geo-grid data, you'd never know where to focus local SEO effort.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is GBP Insights enough for local SEO analytics?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. GBP Insights provides basic impressions and clicks. It cannot show Maps rankings across a geographic radius, compare against competitors, track ranking changes over time, or audit your profile for optimization gaps. For any serious local SEO effort, a dedicated GBP analytics tool is required — BrightLocal at $39/month or theStacc at $49/month are the best starting points.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much do GBP analytics tools cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">GBP analytics tools range from free (GBP Insights) to $299+/month (Birdeye). Budget options: Local Falcon ($24.99/month), Localo ($19–$69/month), Places Scout ($10–$50/month). Mid-range: BrightLocal ($39–$59/month), theStacc Local SEO module ($49/month including automation). Enterprise: Birdeye ($299+/month).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What GBP analytics tool is best for agencies?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">BrightLocal is the best GBP analytics tool for agencies — multi-location management, white-label reporting, client-facing dashboards, and comprehensive data at $39–$59/month per location. theStacc offers a white-label agency program for agencies that want to include automated local SEO alongside analytics. Local Viking's bulk geo-grid scanning is efficient for agencies managing large location portfolios.</div>
